text:
PSA about the new version of channels

1. They're no longer single topics / hashtags. We tried hashtags for a year and they didn't work. There's no canonical /food channel anymore. Instead, there will be many smaller groups about a topic.

2. The best way to think about the new version of channels — a text-based Twitter Space. There's a group of people (members) "on stage" who can post new stuff in the channel, and a larger group in the "audience". However, anyone in the audience can reply and get discovered / invited to the channel. We've improved how replies work (and making it easy to invite from replies) in the last 24 hours.

3. Casting in your home feed, i.e. no channel, will give you just as much distribution in the algo. We have not been boosting casts from channels you follow but people you don't follow for a while. The results were too inconsistent.

4. Our next big focus will be onboarding new users directly to channels when joining Farcaster.

Introducing fargates.mint.club 🚪

A channel moderation tool to set up an invitation gate for your channels.

- Deploy a membership collection that users can mint to receive an invitation
- Set up different "quests" that users can complete to earn an invitation

Different types of "quests" you can set:

1. Follower count / following a user or channel
2. Real user metrics like Farscore / on-chain transaction count / Basename ownership
3. Warpcast-related metrics like liked / recasted a cast
4. Various token ownership checks - holding ERC20 / ERC721 / ERC1155

All memberships are deployed on @base.base.eth via the /mintclub protocol, powered by @neynar & @airstack.eth 🔵⚡️

Let me know in the comments if you need different types of quests 🙏

did my first all day offsite yesterday with the @coinbase exec team. a few quick observations:

1. this is a real team — brian, emilie, alesia, max, & greg have now been working together for 5+ years — and it shows.

I mostly listened and learned — I'm excited to be a part of this team and to bring the perspective I have from being in the onchain trenches every day with all of you.

I think we live in an age where everyone wants everything in an instant, and opinions of others are wanted constantly. But screw that, take your time and knead your dough is what I say. Don’t let others tell you otherwise. Your dough is precious - you don’t have to let others think for you all the time.

Submitting @payflow to Purple x Octant #retropgf

Bootstrapped Payflow to make Onchain Social Payments simple and accessible with many farcaster used tokens, including public goods stablecoin - @glodollar; not VC funded!

- Payflow is PWA integrated through frames, cast actions, bot commands, and mini-apps, also natively into Warpcast Pay.
- Enables P2P payments directly within social feed or app, buying or gifting farcaster storage, collectibles from @zora and @rodeodotclub, with cross-chain payment support for 25+ tokens.
- Aggregates contact book from various social graphs and provides all your payment history made within Payflow.
- Users can claim /degen and @moxie.eth rewards either through the app or as a mini-app on @warpcast and @recaster-fc.
- Payflow offers a single platform to manage all social payments, supporting community tokens and solving real problems not yet addressed by the Farcaster ecosystem

I would greatly appreciate your support in this round!
